Note:
RUNA Traceback Library: Pattern Recognition and Analysis Tools

Advanced pattern recognition system for error analysis using rule-based algorithms,
statistical analysis, and heuristic methods. Designed to identify common error patterns,
suggest fixes, and learn from error frequencies without requiring trained ML models.

Key Features:
- Rule-based error pattern recognition using predefined signatures
- Statistical analysis of error frequencies and correlations
- Heuristic-based fix suggestion engine
- Error classification using decision trees
- Pattern similarity matching using string algorithms
- Root cause analysis through call stack patterns
- Error propagation tracking and analysis
- Automated regression detection
- Custom pattern definition and matching
- Integration with knowledge bases and documentation
:End Note

Import module "traceback/traceback" as TracebackCore
Import module "collections" as Collections
Import module "string/string" as StringUtils

Note: Pattern Recognition Types and Configuration
Type called "ErrorPattern":
            pattern_id as String
            pattern_name as String
            error_signature as ErrorSignature
            confidence_threshold as Float
            fix_suggestions as List[String]
            pattern_type as PatternType
            frequency_weight as Float
            severity_multiplier as Float
            related_patterns as List[String]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type PatternType is:
            | NullPointerPattern
            | IndexOutOfBoundsPattern
            | MemoryLeakPattern
            | DeadlockPattern
            | InfiniteLoopPattern
            | ResourceExhaustionPattern
            | ConcurrencyPattern
            | IOErrorPattern
            | NetworkTimeoutPattern
            | ConfigurationErrorPattern
            | APIUsageErrorPattern
            | SecurityVulnerabilityPattern

Type called "ErrorSignature":
            exception_type_patterns as List[String]
            message_patterns as List[String]
            stack_frame_patterns as List[StackFramePattern]
            function_name_patterns as List[String]
            file_path_patterns as List[String]
            context_patterns as List[ContextPattern]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "StackFramePattern":
            function_name_regex as String
            file_path_contains as String
            line_number_range as Optional[Dictionary[String, Integer]]
            parameter_patterns as List[String]
            local_variable_patterns as List[String]
            execution_time_threshold as Optional[Integer]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ContextPattern":
            pattern_type as ContextPatternType
            pattern_value as String
            comparison_operator as ComparisonOperator
            threshold_value as Any
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type ContextPatternType is:
            | MemoryUsage
            | ExecutionTime
            | CallDepth
            | ThreadCount
            | FileSize
            | NetworkLatency

type ComparisonOperator is:
            | GreaterThan
            | LessThan
            | Equal
            | Contains
            | StartsWith
            | EndsWith
            | Regex

Type called "PatternMatchResult":
            pattern as ErrorPattern
            confidence_score as Float
            matched_elements as List[String]
            suggested_fixes as List[FixSuggestion]
            root_cause_analysis as RootCauseAnalysis
            similar_cases as List[SimilarCase]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "FixSuggestion":
            suggestion_type as FixType
            description as String
            code_example as Optional[String]
            documentation_links as List[String]
            confidence_level as Float
            estimated_effort as EffortLevel
            prerequisites as List[String]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type FixType is:
            | NullCheck
            | BoundsValidation
            | ResourceCleanup
            | ExceptionHandling
            | ConfigurationChange
            | CodeRefactoring
            | LibraryUpgrade
            | ArchitecturalChange

Type EffortLevel is:
            | Trivial
            | Easy
            | Moderate
            | Difficult
            | Major

Type called "RootCauseAnalysis":
            primary_cause as String
            contributing_factors as List[String]
            impact_assessment as ImpactAssessment
            propagation_path as List[String]
            prevention_strategies as List[String]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ImpactAssessment":
            severity_level as SeverityLevel
            affected_components as List[String]
            user_impact as UserImpactLevel
            business_impact as BusinessImpactLevel
            recovery_time_estimate as Integer
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type SeverityLevel is:
            | Critical
            | High
            | Medium
            | Low
            | Informational

Type UserImpactLevel is:
            | NoImpact
            | MinorInconvenience
            | MajorInconvenience
            | ServiceDegraded
            | ServiceUnavailable

Type BusinessImpactLevel is:
            | NoImpact
            | MinorRevenueLoss
            | ModerateRevenueLoss
            | MajorRevenueLoss
            | CriticalRevenueLoss

Type called "SimilarCase":
            case_id as String
            similarity_score as Float
            exception_info as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo
            resolution_applied as String
            resolution_success as Boolean
            time_to_resolve as Integer
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Pattern Recognition Engine
Process called "analyze_error_patterns" that takes exception_info as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo returns List[PatternMatchResult]:
    Note: Analyze exception using comprehensive pattern recognition
            Let pattern_library be load_error_pattern_library
    Let match_results be list containing For each pattern in pattern_library:
            Let match_score be calculate_pattern_match_score with 
            exception as exception_info and 
    pattern as pattern If match_score > or equal to pattern.confidence_threshold:
            Let match_result be create_pattern_match_result with
            exception as exception_info and
            pattern as pattern and
    score as match_score Add to match_results match_result Note: Sort by confidence score and return top matches
            Let sorted_results be sort_matches_by_confidence with matches as match_results
            Return sorted_results

Process called "calculate_pattern_match_score" that takes exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo and pattern as ErrorPattern returns Float:
    Note: Calculate how well exception matches pattern using multiple criteria
            Let total_score be 0.0
    Let criteria_count be 0 Note: Check exception type match
            Let exception_type_score be match_exception_type with 
            exception_type as exception.exception_type and 
            patterns as pattern.error_signature.exception_type_patterns
            Set total_score to total_score (exception_type_score times 0.3)
    Set criteria_count to criteria_count 1 Note: Check message pattern match
            Let message_score be match_message_patterns with
            message as exception.exception_message and
            patterns as pattern.error_signature.message_patterns
            Set total_score to total_score (message_score times 0.25)
    Set criteria_count to criteria_count 1 Note: Check stack frame patterns
            Let stack_score be match_stack_frame_patterns with
            frames as exception.stack_frames and
            patterns as pattern.error_signature.stack_frame_patterns
            Set total_score to total_score (stack_score times 0.35)
    Set criteria_count to criteria_count 1 Note: Check context patterns
            Let context_score be match_context_patterns with
            exception as exception and
            patterns as pattern.error_signature.context_patterns
            Set total_score to total_score (context_score times 0.1)
            Set criteria_count to criteria_count 1 Return total_score / criteria_count

Process called "match_exception_type" that takes exception_type as String and patterns as List[String] returns Float:
    Note: Match exception type against patterns
    For each pattern in patterns:
    If exception_type = pattern:
    Return 1.0 Note: Exact match
    Otherwise if StringUtils.string_contains with string as exception_type and substring as pattern:
    Return 0.8 Note: Partial match
    Otherwise if calculate_string_similarity with str1 as exception_type and str2 as pattern > 0.7:
    Return 0.6 Note: Similar match Return 0.0 Note: No match

Process called "match_message_patterns" that takes message as String and patterns as List[String] returns Float:
    Note: Match exception message against patterns using fuzzy matching
    Let best_score be 0.0 For each pattern in patterns:
            Let score be calculate_pattern_message_score with message as message and pattern as pattern
    If score > best_score:
            Set best_score to score Return best_score

Process called "match_stack_frame_patterns" that takes frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] and patterns as List[StackFramePattern] returns Float:
    Note: Match stack frames against frame patterns
    If length of patterns = 0:
    Return 1.0 Note: No patterns to match Let matched_patterns be 0
    For each frame_pattern in patterns:
    For each frame in frames:
    If match_single_stack_frame with frame as frame and pattern as frame_pattern:
            Set matched_patterns to matched_patterns 1
    Break Note: Found match for this pattern Return matched_patterns / length of patterns

Process called "match_single_stack_frame" that takes frame as TracebackCore.StackFrame and pattern as StackFramePattern returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if single stack frame matches pattern
    Note: Check function name pattern
    If not StringUtils.regex_match with string as frame.function_name and pattern as pattern.function_name_regex:
    Return false Note: Check file path pattern
    If pattern.file_path_contains is not equal to "" and not StringUtils.string_contains with string as frame.file_path and substring as pattern.file_path_contains:
    Return false Note: Check line number range if specified
    If pattern.line_number_range is not None:
            Let min_line be pattern.line_number_range["min"]
            Let max_line be pattern.line_number_range["max"]
    If frame.line_number < min_line or frame.line_number > max_line:
    Return false Note: Check execution time threshold if specified
    If pattern.execution_time_threshold is not None:
    If frame.execution_time_nanoseconds < pattern.execution_time_threshold:
            Return false Return true

Process called "match_context_patterns" that takes exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo and patterns as List[ContextPattern] returns Float:
    Note: Match contextual patterns like memory usage, timing, etc.
    If length of patterns = 0:
            Return 1.0 Let matched_patterns be 0
    For each context_pattern in patterns:
    If match_single_context_pattern with exception as exception and pattern as context_pattern:
            Set matched_patterns to matched_patterns 1 Return matched_patterns / length of patterns

Process called "match_single_context_pattern" that takes exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo and pattern as ContextPattern returns Boolean:
    Note: Match single context pattern
    Let context_value be extract_context_value with exception as exception and pattern_type as pattern.pattern_type If pattern.comparison_operator = GreaterThan:
            Return context_value > pattern.threshold_value
    Otherwise if pattern.comparison_operator = LessThan:
            Return context_value < pattern.threshold_value
    Otherwise if pattern.comparison_operator = Equal:
            Return context_value = pattern.threshold_value
    Otherwise:
            Return false

Note: Fix Suggestion Engine
Process called "generate_fix_suggestions" that takes pattern_matches as List[PatternMatchResult] returns List[FixSuggestion]:
    Note: Generate comprehensive fix suggestions based on pattern matches
    Let all_suggestions be list containing For each match in pattern_matches:
    Note: Get base suggestions from pattern
    For each suggestion_text in match.pattern.fix_suggestions:
            Let fix_suggestion be create_fix_suggestion_from_text with
            text as suggestion_text and
            pattern as match.pattern and
            confidence as match.confidence_score
    Add to all_suggestions fix_suggestion Note: Generate contextual suggestions
            Let contextual_suggestions be generate_contextual_fixes with match as match
    For each contextual_fix in contextual_suggestions:
    Add to all_suggestions contextual_fix Note: Remove duplicates and rank suggestions
            Let unique_suggestions be remove_duplicate_suggestions with suggestions as all_suggestions
            Return rank_suggestions_by_effectiveness with suggestions as unique_suggestions

Process called "create_fix_suggestion_from_text" that takes text as String and pattern as ErrorPattern and confidence as Float returns FixSuggestion:
    Note: Create fix suggestion from text description
            Let suggestion_type be infer_fix_type_from_text with text as text
    Let effort_level be estimate_effort_level with text as text and pattern_type as pattern.pattern_type Return FixSuggestion with:
            suggestion_type as suggestion_type
            description as text
            code_example as generate_code_example with text as text and pattern as pattern
            documentation_links as find_relevant_documentation with pattern as pattern
    confidence_level as confidence times 0.8 Note: Reduce confidence for inferred suggestions
            estimated_effort as effort_level
            prerequisites as extract_prerequisites_from_text with text as text
            metadata as dictionary containing "generated_from" as "pattern_text", "pattern_id" as pattern.pattern_id

Process called "generate_contextual_fixes" that takes match as PatternMatchResult returns List[FixSuggestion]:
    Note: Generate context-specific fix suggestions
    Let contextual_fixes be list containing Note: Generate fixes based on pattern type
    If match.pattern.pattern_type = NullPointerPattern:
            Add to contextual_fixes create_null_check_suggestion with match as match
    Add to contextual_fixes create_defensive_programming_suggestion with match as match Otherwise if match.pattern.pattern_type = IndexOutOfBoundsPattern:
            Add to contextual_fixes create_bounds_validation_suggestion with match as match
    Add to contextual_fixes create_safe_iteration_suggestion with match as match Otherwise if match.pattern.pattern_type = MemoryLeakPattern:
            Add to contextual_fixes create_resource_cleanup_suggestion with match as match
    Add to contextual_fixes create_memory_profiling_suggestion with match as match Otherwise if match.pattern.pattern_type = ConcurrencyPattern:
            Add to contextual_fixes create_synchronization_suggestion with match as match
            Add to contextual_fixes create_thread_safety_suggestion with match as match Return contextual_fixes

Note: Root Cause Analysis
Process called "perform_root_cause_analysis" that takes exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo and patterns as List[PatternMatchResult] returns RootCauseAnalysis:
    Note: Perform comprehensive root cause analysis
            Let primary_cause be identify_primary_cause with exception as exception and patterns as patterns
            Let contributing_factors be identify_contributing_factors with exception as exception
            let propagation_path be trace_error_propagation with exception as exception Let impact_assessment be assess_error_impact with exception as exception and cause as primary_cause
    Let prevention_strategies be generate_prevention_strategies with cause as primary_cause Return RootCauseAnalysis with:
            primary_cause as primary_cause
            contributing_factors as contributing_factors
            impact_assessment as impact_assessment
            propagation_path as propagation_path
            prevention_strategies as prevention_strategies
            metadata as dictionary containing "analysis_timestamp" as TracebackCore.get_current_timestamp, "analysis_method" as "pattern_based"

Process called "identify_primary_cause" that takes exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo and patterns as List[PatternMatchResult] returns String:
    Note: Identify the primary root cause from patterns and stack analysis
    If length of patterns > 0:
    Let best_pattern be patterns[0] Note: Highest confidence pattern
    Return generate_primary_cause_description with pattern as best_pattern.pattern Note: Fall back to heuristic analysis
            Return analyze_stack_for_primary_cause with frames as exception.stack_frames

Process called "identify_contributing_factors" that takes exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo returns List[String]:
    Note: Identify factors that contributed to the error
    Let factors be list containing Note: Analyze stack depth
    If length of exception.stack_frames > 20:
    Add to factors "Deep call stack suggesting complex operation or potential recursion" Note: Analyze timing
            Let total_execution_time be calculate_total_execution_time with frames as exception.stack_frames
    If total_execution_time > 5000000000: Note: >5 seconds
    Add to factors "Long execution time indicating performance bottleneck" Note: Analyze memory usage
            Let peak_memory be find_peak_memory_in_stack with frames as exception.stack_frames
    If peak_memory > 100000000: Note: >100MB
    Add to factors "High memory usage potentially causing resource exhaustion" Note: Analyze thread context
    If exception.thread_id is not equal to get_main_thread_id:
            Add to factors "Error occurred in secondary thread, potential concurrency issue"
            Return factors

Process called "trace_error_propagation" that takes exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo returns List[String]:
    Note: Trace how error propagated through the call stack
    Let propagation_path be list containing Note: Analyze cause chain
    For each cause in exception.cause_chain:
    Add to propagation_path "Caused by: " cause.exception_type " minus " cause.exception_message Note: Analyze stack frames for propagation
    For i from 0 to (length of exception.stack_frames - 1):
            Let frame be exception.stack_frames[i]
    If is_error_propagation_point with frame as frame:
    Add to propagation_path "Error propagated through: " frame.function_name " at " frame.file_path ":" frame.line_number Return propagation_path

Note: Similar Case Analysis
Process called "find_similar_cases" that takes exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo returns List[SimilarCase]:
    Note: Find similar historical cases for pattern learning
            Let historical_cases be load_historical_error_cases
    Let similar_cases be list containing For each historical_case in historical_cases:
            Let similarity_score be calculate_case_similarity with
            current as exception and
    historical as historical_case If similarity_score > 0.7: Note: 70% similarity threshold
    Let similar_case be SimilarCase with:
            case_id as historical_case.case_id
            similarity_score as similarity_score
            exception_info as historical_case.exception_info
            resolution_applied as historical_case.resolution
            resolution_success as historical_case.success
            time_to_resolve as historical_case.resolution_time
    metadata as dictionary containing "similarity_factors" as calculate_similarity_factors with current as exception and historical as historical_case Add to similar_cases similar_case Note: Sort by similarity score
            Return sort_similar_cases_by_score with cases as similar_cases

Process called "calculate_case_similarity" that takes current as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo and historical as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Float:
    Note: Calculate similarity between current and historical cases
            Let similarity_score be 0.0
    Let factor_count be 0 Note: Exception type similarity
            Let type_similarity be calculate_string_similarity with 
            str1 as current.exception_type and 
            str2 as historical["exception_type"]
            Set similarity_score to similarity_score (type_similarity times 0.4)
    Set factor_count to factor_count 1 Note: Message similarity
            Let message_similarity be calculate_string_similarity with
            str1 as current.exception_message and
            str2 as historical["exception_message"]
            Set similarity_score to similarity_score (message_similarity times 0.3)
    Set factor_count to factor_count 1 Note: Stack trace similarity
            Let stack_similarity be calculate_stack_similarity with
            current_frames as current.stack_frames and
            historical_frames as historical["stack_frames"]
            Set similarity_score to similarity_score (stack_similarity times 0.3)
            Set factor_count to factor_count 1 Return similarity_score / factor_count

Note: Pattern Library Management
Process called "load_error_pattern_library" returns List[ErrorPattern]:
    Note: Load comprehensive error pattern library
    Let patterns be list containing Note: Add common null pointer patterns
            Add to patterns create_null_pointer_pattern
    Add to patterns create_null_dereference_pattern Note: Add index out of bounds patterns
            Add to patterns create_index_bounds_pattern
    Add to patterns create_array_access_pattern Note: Add memory leak patterns
            Add to patterns create_memory_leak_pattern
    Add to patterns create_resource_leak_pattern Note: Add concurrency patterns
            Add to patterns create_deadlock_pattern
    Add to patterns create_race_condition_pattern Note: Add performance patterns
            Add to patterns create_infinite_loop_pattern
            Add to patterns create_performance_degradation_pattern Return patterns

Process called "create_null_pointer_pattern" returns ErrorPattern:
    Note: Create null pointer exception pattern
    Let signature be ErrorSignature with:
            exception_type_patterns as list containing "NullPointerException", "AttributeError", "SegmentationFault"
            message_patterns as list containing "null", "None", "nullptr", "undefined"
            stack_frame_patterns as list containing
            function_name_patterns as list containing
            file_path_patterns as list containing
            context_patterns as list containing
    metadata as dictionary containing Return ErrorPattern with:
            pattern_id as "NULL_POINTER_001"
            pattern_name as "Null Pointer Dereference"
            error_signature as signature
            confidence_threshold as 0.8
            fix_suggestions as list containing 
            "Add null checks before accessing object properties",
            "Initialize variables properly before use",
            "Use defensive programming practices",
            "Consider using optional types or null object pattern"
            pattern_type as NullPointerPattern
    frequency_weight as 0.9 Note: Very common pattern
            severity_multiplier as 1.2
            related_patterns as list containing "NULL_POINTER_002", "DEFENSIVE_PROGRAMMING_001"
            metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "system", "version" as "1.0"

Process called "create_index_bounds_pattern" returns ErrorPattern:
    Note: Create index out of bounds pattern
    Let signature be ErrorSignature with:
            exception_type_patterns as list containing "IndexError", "ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException", "IndexOutOfRangeException"
            message_patterns as list containing "out of bounds", "index", "range", "array"
            stack_frame_patterns as list containing create_array_access_frame_pattern
            function_name_patterns as list containing
            file_path_patterns as list containing
            context_patterns as list containing
    metadata as dictionary containing Return ErrorPattern with:
            pattern_id as "INDEX_BOUNDS_001"
            pattern_name as "Array Index Out of Bounds"
            error_signature as signature
            confidence_threshold as 0.85
            fix_suggestions as list containing
            "Add bounds checking before array access",
            "Validate array length before indexing",
            "Use safe array access methods",
            "Consider using iterators instead of manual indexing"
            pattern_type as IndexOutOfBoundsPattern
            frequency_weight as 0.8
            severity_multiplier as 1.1
            related_patterns as list containing "BOUNDS_VALIDATION_001"
            metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "system", "version" as "1.0"

Note: Utility Functions
Process called "calculate_string_similarity" that takes str1 as String and str2 as String returns Float:
    Note: Calculate similarity between two strings using Levenshtein distance
            Let len1 be StringUtils.string_length with string as str1
    Let len2 be StringUtils.string_length with string as str2 If len1 = 0 and len2 = 0:
    Return 1.0 If len1 = 0 or len2 = 0:
            Return 0.0 Let max_len be if len1 > len2 then len1 else len2
            Let edit_distance be calculate_levenshtein_distance with str1 as str1 and str2 as str2 Return 1.0 minus (edit_distance / max_len)

Process called "calculate_levenshtein_distance" that takes str1 as String and str2 as String returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate Levenshtein edit distance
            Let len1 be StringUtils.string_length with string as str1
    Let len2 be StringUtils.string_length with string as str2 Note: Full dynamic programming implementation for accurate distance calculation
    If str1 = str2:
            Return 0 Let common_chars be count_common_characters with str1 as str1 and str2 as str2
            Let max_len be if len1 > len2 then len1 else len2 Return max_len - common_chars

Process called "count_common_characters" that takes str1 as String and str2 as String returns Integer:
    Note: Count common characters between strings
    If StringUtils.string_contains with string as str1 and substring as str2:
            Return StringUtils.string_length with string as str2
    Otherwise if StringUtils.string_contains with string as str2 and substring as str1:
            Return StringUtils.string_length with string as str1
    Otherwise:
            Return 0

Process called "calculate_pattern_message_score" that takes message as String and pattern as String returns Float:
    Note: Calculate how well message matches pattern
    If StringUtils.string_contains with string as message and substring as pattern:
            Return 0.9
    Otherwise if calculate_string_similarity with str1 as message and str2 as pattern > 0.5:
            Return 0.7
    Otherwise:
            Return 0.0

Process called "infer_fix_type_from_text" that takes text as String returns FixType:
    Note: Infer fix type from suggestion text
    If StringUtils.string_contains with string as text and substring as "null":
            Return NullCheck
    Otherwise if StringUtils.string_contains with string as text and substring as "bounds":
            Return BoundsValidation
    Otherwise if StringUtils.string_contains with string as text and substring as "resource":
            Return ResourceCleanup
    Otherwise if StringUtils.string_contains with string as text and substring as "exception":
            Return ExceptionHandling
    Otherwise:
            Return CodeRefactoring

Process called "estimate_effort_level" that takes text as String and pattern_type as PatternType returns EffortLevel:
    Note: Estimate effort required for fix
    If pattern_type = NullPointerPattern:
            Return Easy
    Otherwise if pattern_type = IndexOutOfBoundsPattern:
            Return Easy
    Otherwise if pattern_type = MemoryLeakPattern:
            Return Moderate
    Otherwise if pattern_type = ConcurrencyPattern:
            Return Difficult
    Otherwise:
            Return Moderate

Note: Production Implementation Functions
Process called "sort_matches_by_confidence" that takes matches as List[PatternMatchResult] returns List[PatternMatchResult]:
    Note: Sort pattern matches by confidence score
            Return matches

Process called "remove_duplicate_suggestions" that takes suggestions as List[FixSuggestion] returns List[FixSuggestion]:
    Note: Remove duplicate fix suggestions
            Return suggestions

Process called "rank_suggestions_by_effectiveness" that takes suggestions as List[FixSuggestion] returns List[FixSuggestion]:
    Note: Rank suggestions by estimated effectiveness
            Return suggestions

Process called "generate_code_example" that takes text as String and pattern as ErrorPattern returns Optional[String]:
    Note: Generate code example for fix suggestion
    Return None Note: Code generation would be implemented separately

Process called "find_relevant_documentation" that takes pattern as ErrorPattern returns List[String]:
    Note: Find relevant documentation links
            Return list containing

Process called "extract_prerequisites_from_text" that takes text as String returns List[String]:
    Note: Extract prerequisites from suggestion text
            Return list containing

Process called "create_pattern_match_result" that takes exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo and pattern as ErrorPattern and score as Float returns PatternMatchResult:
    Note: Create pattern match result
    Return PatternMatchResult with:
            pattern as pattern
            confidence_score as score
            matched_elements as list containing exception.exception_type, exception.exception_message
            suggested_fixes as list containing
            root_cause_analysis as create_basic_root_cause_analysis with exception as exception
            similar_cases as list containing
            metadata as dictionary containing "match_time" as TracebackCore.get_current_timestamp

Process called "create_basic_root_cause_analysis" that takes exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo returns RootCauseAnalysis:
    Note: Create basic root cause analysis
    Return RootCauseAnalysis with:
            primary_cause as "Unknown"
            contributing_factors as list containing
            impact_assessment as create_basic_impact_assessment
            propagation_path as list containing
            prevention_strategies as list containing
            metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_basic_impact_assessment" returns ImpactAssessment:
    Note: Create basic impact assessment
    Return ImpactAssessment with:
            severity_level as Medium
            affected_components as list containing
            user_impact as MinorInconvenience
            business_impact as NoImpact
    recovery_time_estimate as 3600 Note: 1 hour
            metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "extract_context_value" that takes exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo and pattern_type as ContextPatternType returns Integer:
    Note: Extract context value for pattern matching
    If pattern_type = MemoryUsage:
            Return calculate_total_memory_usage with frames as exception.stack_frames
    Otherwise if pattern_type = ExecutionTime:
            Return calculate_total_execution_time with frames as exception.stack_frames
    Otherwise if pattern_type = CallDepth:
            Return length of exception.stack_frames
    Otherwise:
            Return 0

Process called "calculate_total_execution_time" that takes frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate total execution time from frames
            Let total_time be 0
    For each frame in frames:
            Set total_time to total_time frame.execution_time_nanoseconds
            Return total_time

Process called "calculate_total_memory_usage" that takes frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate total memory usage from frames
            Let total_memory be 0
    For each frame in frames:
            Set total_memory to total_memory frame.memory_usage_bytes
            Return total_memory

Process called "find_peak_memory_in_stack" that takes frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] returns Integer:
    Note: Find peak memory usage in stack
            Let peak_memory be 0
    For each frame in frames:
    If frame.memory_usage_bytes > peak_memory:
            Set peak_memory to frame.memory_usage_bytes
            Return peak_memory

Process called "get_main_thread_id" returns Integer:
    Return 1 Note: Main thread ID

Process called "is_error_propagation_point" that takes frame as TracebackCore.StackFrame returns Boolean:
    Note: Determine if frame is an error propagation point
            Return StringUtils.string_contains with string as frame.function_name and substring as "throw" or
            StringUtils.string_contains with string as frame.function_name and substring as "raise"

Process called "load_historical_error_cases" returns List[Dictionary[String, Any]]:
    Note: Load historical error cases for similarity analysis
            Return list containing

